wht is the best instore product to clean shine and restore hardwood floors my hardwood floors are so dull and dirty looking i tried murphys oil soap that didn't touch it without renting a buffer or polisher is there any good products out on the shelves now that will restore the shine and hide tiny scratch marks i need an answer fast with company coming next week wood floor maintenance most wood floors can be kept clean by first sweeping or vacuuming with a floor nozzle to remove most of the surface dust and dirt then damp mopping with clear water dip a sponge in clear water squeezing it out so that the mop is barely damp almost dry use very little water and rinse your mop thoroughly after each use since excess water can dissolve protective coatings alter the color of the wood and raise the grain to roughen the surface if your floors are not dirty enough to need mopping every week then you should not do it as it will wear the floors faster not to mention waste your time simply sweeping is often all they need if need to restore the shine to your wood floor after you get it clean try damp mopping it with cup vinegar and tablespoons furniture polish in a gallon of warm water vinegar is also useful for removing any soap residue or build up but should not be necessary every week Upholstery Vacuum cleaner Soap Brewery Menstrual cup Car washing techniques Gilding Dry cleaning Manicure Dishwasher Casting Wood Diving suit Wok Violin Dairy Lighting Drill bit Hard disk Printmaking Coffee Hemp Friction Textile manufacturing Opportunity rover Dishwashing Sento Carburetor Sulfuric acid Soap bubble Hard water Pottery Biodiesel E85 Motor oil Knife Shampoo Soldering Sewage treatment Carbon dioxide sink Thermal power station Wood carving Fire fighting Seismic retrofit Cast iron Military history of the United Kingdom during World War II Shoe Fossil fuel power plant Hamster Bong Wind turbine Carbon dioxide Bulk vending Printed circuit board Paint Kitchen Tobacco Lacquer M16 (rifle) Tofu